### InkWall API — VS Code REST Client
### Usage: set @token after logging in (copy from the login response)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@token = paste_jwt_here
@refreshToken = paste_refresh_token_here

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# AUTH
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### Register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Login  ← copy token + refreshToken from response into variables above
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jhhojh10@gmail.com",
  "password": "qwe123"
}

### Refresh access token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### Google OAuth — open this URL in a browser, not via REST Client
# GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/google

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# USERS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get own profile (with interests, following, followers)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update own interests (array of topic ObjectIds)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "interests": ["64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0", "64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c1"]
}

### Change password (email/password accounts only)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/me/password
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "qwe123",
  "newPassword": "newpass456"
}

### Upload avatar — use a REST client that supports multipart, or Swagger at /api-docs
# POST {{baseUrl}}/users/me/avatar  (multipart/form-data, field: image)

### Get recommended users (up to 5, based on shared interests)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/recommended
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Follow a user
POST {{baseUrl}}/users/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0/follow
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Unfollow a user
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0/follow
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List all users (paginated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=1&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get user by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Delete user by ID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# POSTS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### List posts (paginated; filter by topics or authorIds)
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### List posts filtered by topic and author
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts?topics[]=64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0&authorIds[]=64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get post by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/posts/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create post
POST {{baseUrl}}/posts
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "My First Post",
  "text": "This is the body of my post written in **Markdown**.",
  "image": "",
  "topics": ["64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0"]
}

### Update post (owner only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/posts/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated Title",
  "text": "Updated body content."
}

### Delete post (owner only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/posts/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# FILE UPLOAD
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### Upload image — returns { url: "/uploads/<filename>" }
### Use Swagger UI at http://localhost:5000/api-docs or a multipart-capable client
# POST {{baseUrl}}/upload  (multipart/form-data, field: image)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# COMMENTS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### List all comments (paginated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/comments?page=1&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get comment by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/comments/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create comment
POST {{baseUrl}}/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "postId": "64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0",
  "content": "Great article, thanks for sharing!"
}

### Update comment (owner only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/comments/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Edited: even better article!"
}

### Delete comment (owner only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/comments/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# LIKES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### List all likes
GET {{baseUrl}}/likes?page=1&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Like a post (postId required; omit commentId for post likes)
POST {{baseUrl}}/likes
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "postId": "64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0"
}

### Remove a like
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/likes/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# TOPICS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### List all topics
GET {{baseUrl}}/topics
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get topic by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/topics/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# CHATS
# Real-time: clients join "join_user_room" (userId) on mount
# and "join_chat" (chatId) when a chat is opened.
# POST /chats is find-or-create: 200 = existing, 201 = new
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### List all chats (admin/debug)
GET {{baseUrl}}/chats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get all chats for a user — sorted by most recent activity
GET {{baseUrl}}/chats/user/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get chat by ID (includes embedded messages array)
GET {{baseUrl}}/chats/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create or retrieve 1-on-1 chat (find-or-create)
### Returns 201 for a new chat, 200 if one already exists between the two users
### The authenticated user is added to participants automatically
POST {{baseUrl}}/chats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Chat with alice@example.com",
  "participants": ["64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c1"]
}

### Create a group chat
POST {{baseUrl}}/chats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Study Group",
  "participants": ["64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c1", "64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c2"]
}

### Delete chat (participants only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/chats/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# MESSAGES
# Sending a message also:
#   • touches chat.updatedAt (sidebar sort)
#   • emits "new_message" → chat room
#   • emits "chat_list_update" → each participant's personal room
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### List messages (optionally filter by chatId)
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages?chatId=64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0&page=1&limit=50
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get message by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/messages/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Send a message (participants only — triggers Socket.io broadcasts)
POST {{baseUrl}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "chatId": "64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0",
  "content": "Hello everyone!"
}

### Delete message (sender only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/messages/64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# AI WRITING ASSISTANCE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### AI assist — improve, continue, or outline a post draft
POST {{baseUrl}}/ai/assist
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "The Future of Web Development",
  "content": "Web development has changed a lot over the past decade...",
  "instruction": "improve"
}

### AI summarize — generate a 2-3 sentence summary
POST {{baseUrl}}/ai/summarize
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "The Future of Web Development",
  "content": "Web development has changed a lot over the past decade. React, Vue, and other frameworks..."
}

### AI suggest-topics — returns array of matching topic ObjectIds
POST {{baseUrl}}/ai/suggest-topics
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Getting started with TypeScript",
  "content": "TypeScript adds static types to JavaScript, making large codebases easier to maintain...",
  "topics": [
    { "_id": "64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0", "name": "Technology" },
    { "_id": "64e2f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c1", "name": "Programming" }
  ]
}
